<div class="quotetitle">Boolean wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><br />Why does some game read the controller twice?<br /></div>The <a href="http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/APU_DMC" class="postlink">APU DMC</a> can <a href="http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/Standard_controller#Evil_Details" class="postlink">interfere with controller reading</a>. To ensure the correct value has been read, most games using the DMC channel will read the controller at least twice.<br /><div class="quotetitle">Boolean wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><br />Is it necessary to do that when I write an NES demo?<br /></div>Only if you use the DMC.<br /><div class="quotetitle">Boolean wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><br />Is there any case where a game read controller three(or more) times in history?<br /></div>Yes. From <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=8217" class="postlink">this thread</a>:<br /><ul><li>Super Mario Bros. 3</li><li>Batman</li><li>Tetris</li></ul><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=5948">Joe</a> — Sun Aug 31, 2014 8:19 am</p><hr />
